First try the local flaps, especially NAPA. If you are lucky they will give
you a small capsule with some dizzy grease inside. I forgot the part number
but it is in their catalog at least as of last year.

If you strike out you can buy a lifetime supply of Bosch grease from Pelican
Parts or Gene Berg.

http://www.pelicanparts.com/catalog/shopcart/9144/POR_9144_igniti_pg2.htm
Q1060001

http://www.geneberg.com/elctrcpg10.htm
BSH5700002005 

